&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;I failed to preview LaTeX with &lt;code&gt;emacs-plus&lt;/code&gt;. If you have installed &lt;code&gt;d12frosted/emacs-plus&lt;/code&gt;, uninstall it and use &lt;code&gt;emacs-mac&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Deploy Nikola Org Mode on Travis</title><link>https://fromkk.com/posts/deploy-nikola-org-mode-on-travis/</link><pubDate>Sat, 03 Nov 2018 21:20:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://fromkk.com/posts/deploy-nikola-org-mode-on-travis/</guid><category domain="https://fromkk.com/categories/programming/">Programming</category><description>&lt;p&gt;Recently, I enjoy using &lt;code&gt;Spacemacs&lt;/code&gt;, so I decided to switch to org file from Markdown for writing blog. After several attempts, I managed to let Travis convert org file to HTML. Here are the steps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class="heading-element" id="install-org-mode-plugin"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Install Org Mode plugin&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a href="#install-org-mode-plugin" class="heading-mark"&gt;
 &lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;First you need to install Org Mode plugin on your computer following the official guide: &lt;a href="https://plugins.getnikola.com/v8/orgmode/" target="_blank" rel="external nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;Nikola orgmode plugin&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>